* In France, the SNEP said that LP sales were 200,000 in 2008, however independent record labels said that overall sales were probably 1 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.numerama.com/magazine/11655-face-au-cd-en-declin-le-disque-vinyle-fait-un-retour-en-force.html|title=Face au CD en déclin, le disque vinyle fait un retour en force - Business - Numerama|first=Guillaume|last=Champeau|date=9 January 2009|website=Numerama.com|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref>
* In United States, 67% of all vinyl album sales in 2012 were sold at independent music stores.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/01/04/despite-pandora-spotify-total-u-s-music-sales-grew-in-2012/|title=Despite Pandora & Spotify, total U.S. music sales grew in 2012|website=Venturebeat.com|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref>
* Vinyl revenues were at the lowest point in its history in 2006, with a total trade value of $36 million. The 2011 figure of $116 million, is higher than the 2000 figure of $109 million, but is still less than the 1997, 1998 and 1999 figures which were all between $150–$170 million.<ref name="theregister.co.uk"/></small>
